{"key":"post-6224259","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6224259</id>\n<content>I've found that exposed grains on top are more likely to contaminate over time by being exposed.  Of course if you're going to cover it with a casing layer at full colonization, no problem, but for uncased bulk substrates, I prefer to cover all the grains with at least some of the manure or compost, etc.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As agar said, if you're going to sprinkle grains on top, make them very well spread out.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6224553</next>\n<prev>6224117</prev>\n<first>6223901</first>\n<last>6225306</last>\n<when>1162160541</when>\n<utime>10/30/06 12:22 AM</utime>\n</post>"}